<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="12" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="12">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mycetophagidae" genus="Mycetophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mycetophagus flexuosus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">Mycetophagus flexuosus</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded in the Maritime Provinces from New Brunswick (Fig. 1). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cline, AR" journalOrPublisher="Southeastern Naturalist" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="409 - 420" title="Coleoptera associated with the oyster mushroom, Pleurotus ostreatus Fries, in North America." volume="4" year="2005">Cline and Leshen (2005)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it from oyster mushroom (
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pleurotaceae" genus="Pleurotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pleurotus ostreatus" order="Agaricales" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ostreatus">Pleurotus ostreatus</taxonomicName>
) Fries; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weiss, HB" journalOrPublisher="Psyche" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="137 - 139" title="Coleoptera associated with Polyporus versicolor L. in New Jersey." volume="27" year="1920">Weiss (1920)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it from turkey-tail polypore (
<taxonomicName genus="Tramates" lsidName="Tramates versicolor" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" rank="species" species="versicolor">Tramates versicolor</taxonomicName>
(Fr.) Pil.); and 
<bibRefCitation author="Minch, EL" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the New York Entomological Society" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="31 - 35" title="Insect inhabitants of Polyporus betulinus." volume="60" year="1952">Minch (1952)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pielou, DP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Theoretical Biology" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" pagination="201 - 216" title="Association among species of infrequent occurrence: the insect and spider fauna of Polyporus betulinus (Bulliard) Fries." volume="21" year="1968">Pielou and Pielou (1968)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it from birch polypore (
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fomitopsidaceae" genus="Piptoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Piptoporus betulinus" order="Polyporales" pageId="3" pageNumber="12" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="betulinus">Piptoporus betulinus</taxonomicName>
) (Fr.) Kar.
</paragraph>
